exploit_db.help_flags: Here are all the flags you can use:
exploit_db.syntax_error: Something seems to be wrong with your Syntax!
exploit_db.wrong_type: You have entered a wrong type.
exploit_db.wrong_platform: You have entered a wrong Platform, allowed Platforms are:
exploit_db.wrong_tag: You have entered a wrong tag, allowed tags are:
exploit_db.help_flags_title: A part of the title of your exploit
exploit_db.help_flags_cve: The CVE Number of your exploit, both CVE-xxxx-xxxx and xxxx-xxxxx supported.
exploit_db.help_flags_type: The type of your exploit, use `-Help Type` to see allowed values
exploit_db.help_flags_platform: The platform your exploit is for, use `-Help Platform` to see allowed values
exploit_db.help_flags_port: The Port your exploit is for, allowed Values are 1 - 65535, though not all will have results.
exploit_db.help_flags_tag: Tag of your exploit, use `-Help Tag` to see allowed values
exploit_db.help_flags_other:
If you use a flag twice the second value is used.
If you don't use any flags, -Title will be used.
